name: SpeechRecognitionResult.isFinal
description: The isFinal read-only property of the SpeechRecognitionResult interface is a Boolean that states whether this result is final (true) or not (false) — if so, then this is the final time this result will be returned; if not, then this result is an interim result, and may be updated later on.
